# POM Authorship Protection

## Mandatory Rule

Human-authored POM methods and locators are **strictly read-only**. Check the `@author` JSDoc tag before making any change.

### Allowed

- ADD new methods/locators with `@author AI Agent`
- MODIFY methods that have `@author AI Agent`

### Forbidden

- Modifying methods with any human `@author` (Deepak Bohra, Avanish Srivastava, Mukul Khan, etc.)
- Changing human-written locator assignments in constructors
- Reformatting or "improving" human-written code (e.g., converting XPath to getByRole)

### If a Human Locator Needs Fixing

Propose the fix as a code comment — do not apply it:

```typescript
// SUGGESTED FIX (human-authored, do not auto-apply):
// this.matchVendor_LOC = page.getByRole("row", { name: /Match Vendor/i }).locator("td").nth(1);
```
